00:01:36,410 --> 00:01:38,600
[Episode 15]

3
00:01:38,890 --> 00:01:41,289
[Mom]

4
00:01:41,310 --> 00:01:43,590
[Accidents Always Catch You Off Guard]

5
00:01:49,789 --> 00:01:50,550
Sweetie.

6
00:01:50,780 --> 00:01:52,820
Your Aunt Wang said she saw some photos of you.

7
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,740
I asked her, but she wouldn't tell me.

8
00:01:54,990 --> 00:01:56,539
What's going on exactly?

9
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:02,370
Bai Guo.

10
00:02:03,510 --> 00:02:04,310
Mentor.

11
00:02:04,650 --> 00:02:05,460
Bai Guo.

12
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:25,650
Bai Guo!

13
00:02:25,690 --> 00:02:26,880
Mentor!

14
00:02:27,930 --> 00:02:29,410
Mentor!

15
00:02:51,350 --> 00:02:53,710
You haven't said a word since we got back from the hospital.

16
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:56,550
Don't hold it in.

17
00:02:57,610 --> 00:03:00,370
If you want to cry, just let it out.

18
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:12,150
It was a living, breathing life!

19
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:15,010
Such a lovely young woman.

20
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:18,120
I watched her die right in front of me,

21
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:20,050
again and again.

22
00:03:23,930 --> 00:03:25,130
In that space,

23
00:03:25,130 --> 00:03:26,450
I'm a failure.

24
00:03:27,530 --> 00:03:28,650
If nothing can be changed,

25
00:03:28,650 --> 00:03:30,040
why did they send me back?

26
00:03:33,050 --> 00:03:33,829
Gu Nian.

27
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:35,600
Be brave.

28
00:03:38,210 --> 00:03:39,329
We did our best.

29
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:41,290
Gu Nian.

30
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,760
What on earth is the point of living?

31
00:03:47,130 --> 00:03:49,210
Why do we have to suffer like this?

32
00:03:50,370 --> 00:03:52,620
It's endless. Just endless.

33
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,600
Even though we don't know why we live,

34
00:04:00,130 --> 00:04:02,210
since we are alive, we should be brave.

35
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,050
Gu Nian.

36
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:09,400
Although we failed to save her,

37
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:12,720
there's one thing we must do.

38
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,000
What's that?

39
00:04:18,230 --> 00:04:19,279
Clear her name.

40
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,409
Take a look at this, everyone.

41
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,050
There's an anonymous email.

42
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:42,490
It's a chat log between Bai Guo and Ye Weijian.

43
00:04:43,210 --> 00:04:45,340
[Ye Weijian took advantage of his position to sexually harass and exploit his colleague Bai Guo for a year]

44
00:04:45,010 --> 00:04:47,090
So it turns out Mr. Ye is the real scumbag.

45
00:04:47,090 --> 00:04:48,710
Why was Bai Guo so naive?

46
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:51,200
She should have called the police. What couldn't she say?

47
00:04:51,730 --> 00:04:54,130
I can't handle this. Ever since I had my daughter,

48
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:56,010
I can't stand seeing things like this.

49
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:58,130
How could Bai Guo's parents deal with this?

50
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:00,210
Look how outrageous his words are.

51
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,000
I can't believe this happened.

52
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,680
Why did she have to take it to heart?

53
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:06,280
Only when Bai Guo's mother showed me her diary from before she died

54
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:07,640
did I realize

55
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:08,720
that she had been planning

56
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,970
to expose Ye Weijian's worst to the public.

57
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:13,170
Let's help her get this done.

58
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:15,370
I hope there won't be another Bai Guo in this world.

59
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:47,630
Be careful!

60
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:57,000
Huanan!

61
00:05:57,730 --> 00:05:59,200
Huanan! Huanan!

62
00:05:59,390 --> 00:06:00,440
Huanan, are you okay?

63
00:06:00,850 --> 00:06:01,660
I'm okay.

64
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:07,720
Is this 911?

65
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:16,200
Coming.

66
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:18,480
Coming.

67
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:24,840
What happened?

68
00:06:25,860 --> 00:06:26,540
It's nothing.

69
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:27,480
He's injured.

70
00:06:27,710 --> 00:06:28,630
Sit down, sit down.

71
00:06:29,450 --> 00:06:30,600
What happened to you?

72
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,080
It's okay. I'm alright.

73
00:06:34,050 --> 00:06:34,850
What happened?

74
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:38,120
It's nothing. I just bumped into something accidentally.

75
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:44,960
Feng Huanan.

76
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:49,250
Have you been living here since you quit your job?

77
00:06:50,940 --> 00:06:52,730
So which room do you live in?

78
00:06:52,770 --> 00:06:53,850
Go inside and rest.

79
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,200
You sleep here?

80
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:03,000
Well...

81
00:07:03,650 --> 00:07:05,410
I should probably go back to my room.

82
00:07:05,850 --> 00:07:07,970
I... I still have some work to finish.

83
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:09,400
You two talk.

84
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:10,210
You two continue.

85
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,600
Feng Huanan.

86
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,360
Actually,

87
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:21,430
your current situation is largely my fault.

88
00:07:21,810 --> 00:07:23,200
How is it your fault?

89
00:07:23,370 --> 00:07:24,600
Let me tell you, Gu Nian,

90
00:07:24,890 --> 00:07:25,800
you're amazing.

91
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:29,200
I think I'm pretty amazing too.

92
00:07:30,170 --> 00:07:31,240
I never expected

93
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:33,600
that one day you'd become so brave.

94
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:36,040
I'm also inspired

95
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:36,920
by your courage.

96
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:38,280
Now,

97
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:42,409
you're the one guiding me forward.

98
00:07:44,090 --> 00:07:44,909
But...

99
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:47,450
Bai Guo still died.

100
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:49,490
I failed to save her.

101
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,560
Don't feel too guilty.

102
00:07:56,050 --> 00:07:57,280
You've already

103
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,470
given it your all, one hundred percent.

104
00:08:11,230 --> 00:08:12,810
[Mom]

105
00:08:15,330 --> 00:08:15,970
Mom.

106
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:22,800
Hey, Mom.

107
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:24,600
How many times have I told you that

108
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:29,760
things would never work out between Yongfang and I?

109
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:31,570
You always think that

110
00:08:31,570 --> 00:08:33,159
since we grew up together

111
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,090
and she's good to you,

112
00:08:34,110 --> 00:08:35,429
we should be together.

113
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:37,320
But from the beginning to the end,

114
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,679
I've never had feelings for her.

115
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:42,400
I've always seen her as a younger sister.

116
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:45,280
And haven't I told you that

117
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:47,040
I have a girlfriend now?

118
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:49,480
Her name is Gu Nian.

119
00:08:56,060 --> 00:08:57,310
Alright, I'm done talking.

120
00:08:58,010 --> 00:08:59,600
I'm with my girlfriend right now.

121
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:02,950
So stop trying to play matchmaker, okay?

122
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:06,390
Bye-bye.

123
00:09:15,610 --> 00:09:16,490
I'm sorry.

124
00:09:17,370 --> 00:09:18,720
My mom was trying to play matchmaker,

125
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:20,600
so I got anxious, and I...

126
00:09:21,090 --> 00:09:21,890
Well,

127
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,280
I noticed there's some bruising on your leg.

128
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:28,280
Do you want me to help you apply some ointment?

129
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,040
It's alright.

130
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:30,600
Right? Look.

131
00:09:33,190 --> 00:09:33,990
It's just a minor injury.

132
00:09:34,470 --> 00:09:35,680
It should heal in a couple of days.

133
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:42,200
I think it's an interview call.

134
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:43,240
I'll go take it.

135
00:09:43,770 --> 00:09:44,410
Okay.

136
00:09:53,450 --> 00:09:54,840
I'm going to meet an investor later.

137
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,040
It could be of help to you.

138
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:57,360
Are you free to come over?

139
00:09:58,290 --> 00:10:01,050
Sure, sure, no problem.

140
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,200
The usual place.

141
00:10:02,590 --> 00:10:03,810
Okay, I understand.

142
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:11,280
Well, why don't you take care of your business today?

143
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,640
I'll head back first.

144
00:10:12,810 --> 00:10:15,400
I'll come see you again in a couple of days.

145
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,770
You haven't eaten anything tonight.

146
00:10:16,770 --> 00:10:17,650
You must be hungry.

147
00:10:17,770 --> 00:10:19,440
I have a lot of food here.

148
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:20,090
Let me make you some noodles.

149
00:10:20,090 --> 00:10:21,050
No, no need.

150
00:10:21,050 --> 00:10:22,960
Well, I'll be off then.

151
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:26,710
Well, your leg...

152
00:10:26,710 --> 00:10:28,800
Are you sure you don't need to apply some ointment to it?

153
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:31,970
My leg is fine. Are you sure you don't want to eat something?

154
00:10:31,970 --> 00:10:33,200
I'm a good cook, you know.

155
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,200
No, really. There's no need.

156
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:36,960
Well...

157
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:40,010
Have some rest.

158
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,410
I... I'll be going then. Bye-bye.

159
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:43,820
Be careful.

160
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:46,760
I'm off then.

161
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:48,370
Bye-bye.

162
00:10:48,530 --> 00:10:49,170
Bye-bye.

163
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:09,200
So you played a hero, saving the damsel in distress?

164
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:12,010
Stop with the sarcasm.

165
00:11:12,010 --> 00:11:12,920
Help me apply some ointment, will you?

166
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:13,280
Alright.

167
00:11:18,540 --> 00:11:19,270
Tu.

168
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:20,850
I didn't expect you'd still be willing to help me.

169
00:11:22,010 --> 00:11:23,040
Walk with me for a bit.

170
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:25,710
How have you been lately?

171
00:11:31,780 --> 00:11:33,420
I've always loved the sea,

172
00:11:35,010 --> 00:11:37,800
because I can hide my worries there.

