00:13:25,690 --> 00:13:26,760
In the early hours of last night,

182
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:28,890
a man surnamed Ye drove drunk and plunged into a river.

183
00:13:29,330 --> 00:13:31,970
His blood alcohol level was over the limit when he drowned.

184
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:34,170
Take a look at this.

185
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,560
Isn't this Mr. Ye's car?

186
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:36,640
He died from drunk driving?

187
00:13:36,810 --> 00:13:37,710
It really is.

188
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:40,280
Karma comes around. Heaven spares no one.

189
00:13:40,890 --> 00:13:42,410
That scumbag actually died.

190
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:43,800
He got what he deserved.

191
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:45,090
But dying such a quick death,

192
00:13:45,210 --> 00:13:46,120
he got off easy.

193
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:46,790
If you ask me,

194
00:13:46,930 --> 00:13:48,080
this kind of person should be exposed and condemned online.

195
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:50,010
Bai Guo, you can rest in peace now.

196
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,210
It's a pity Bai Guo isn't here.

197
00:13:54,450 --> 00:13:55,970
Otherwise, it would be so satisfying.

198
00:13:57,630 --> 00:13:59,110
It really is instant karma, right?

199
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:00,110
Indeed.

200
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,400
Let's go, stop looking.

201
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:05,280
Let's go eat.

202
00:14:05,590 --> 00:14:06,800
Nian, are you coming with us?

203
00:14:06,860 --> 00:14:07,940
I, uh...

204
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:11,760
Feng, why are you here?

205
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:14,720
My new company is right downstairs,

206
00:14:14,890 --> 00:14:16,890
and I happened to see Gu Nian's takeout,

207
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:18,290
so I brought it up for her.

208
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:20,170
But of course, it was mainly because I missed you all,

209
00:14:20,190 --> 00:14:21,270
and I thought I'd come to see you.

210
00:14:22,490 --> 00:14:24,160
Are you here to see us or Nian?

211
00:14:24,460 --> 00:14:25,390
Let's go. Let's go.

212
00:14:25,570 --> 00:14:27,530
Am I the kind of person who values romance over friendship?

213
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:28,450
Sure you are.

214
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:35,890
Wait.

215
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,360
When did you join a new company?

216
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,890
Why didn't you tell me?

217
00:14:39,410 --> 00:14:40,970
I wanted to give you a surprise.

218
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:43,480
What kind of company is it?

219
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:46,160
It's a small company.

220
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:47,860
You've definitely never heard of it.

221
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:49,800
It's far inferior to Shiyi.

222
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:51,680
But there's one particularly good thing

223
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:53,370
about our company.

224
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:57,050
That is, I can talk to my boss

225
00:14:58,450 --> 00:14:59,570
directly.

226
00:15:00,010 --> 00:15:02,000
Because we don't have any CEOs,

227
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:04,610
presidents, general managers, or any of that stuff.

228
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,000
It's much more efficient to work there.

229
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:11,400
And there's another reason,

230
00:15:12,970 --> 00:15:14,010
that is it's not far from you.

231
00:15:14,770 --> 00:15:16,320
After that incident with Ye Weijian last time,

232
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:18,000
I've been constantly worried about you.

233
00:15:19,050 --> 00:15:21,280
Sometimes, the more I think about it, the more scared I get.

234
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:24,010
What if I hadn't been by your side then?

235
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:28,610
I don't even know what the worst outcome could have been.

236
00:15:30,690 --> 00:15:32,080
Don't worry.

237
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:35,290
It was only because I lost my motorcycle

238
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,210
and I had to take the subway every day

239
00:15:37,210 --> 00:15:38,360
that he took advantage of it.

240
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:39,560
I've thought it through.

241
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:40,960
I'm going to work hard, earn money myself,

242
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,640
and buy a new motorcycle.

243
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:43,760
That way, no one will be able to catch up with me.

244
00:15:43,790 --> 00:15:44,350
Is that so?

245
00:15:47,210 --> 00:15:48,720
So even I can't catch up with you?

246
00:16:01,040 --> 00:16:02,410
I was just kidding.

247
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:05,480
I don't even have a bicycle now.

248
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:06,570
How could I possibly catch up with you?

249
00:16:08,940 --> 00:16:10,500
But don't worry, Gu Nian.

250
00:16:10,650 --> 00:16:11,680
This is only temporary.

251
00:16:11,970 --> 00:16:14,120
I've never given up on my entrepreneurial plan.

252
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:16,050
What I'm doing now

253
00:16:16,050 --> 00:16:18,450
is trying my best to accumulate capital.

254
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,830
I believe as long as I work hard enough,

255
00:16:21,540 --> 00:16:23,740
I'll achieve this goal one day.

256
00:16:26,990 --> 00:16:28,870
Do you have a business plan?

257
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:30,570
Yes, why?

258
00:16:38,590 --> 00:16:39,220
Thank you.

259
00:17:12,970 --> 00:17:15,210
This... This is my motorcycle?

260
00:17:16,079 --> 00:17:18,089
I waited at the trading market for a few days, right?

261
00:17:18,359 --> 00:17:20,560
I can't believe I actually caught it.

262
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:21,240
At first, I thought

263
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:22,609
I must find out which bastard it was who stole it.

264
00:17:22,609 --> 00:17:23,760
I had to report it to the police, right?

265
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,079
But the shopkeeper said it changed hands too many times,

266
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:26,829
so it couldn't be traced.

267
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:28,520
Take a look. Is this still your motorcycle or not?

268
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:29,350
Is anything missing or damaged?

269
00:17:30,330 --> 00:17:32,040
It's exactly the same as before.

270
00:17:34,170 --> 00:17:35,520
You've been injured recently.

271
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:38,390
You didn't spend all your break time staking it out, did you?

272
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:43,210
How much did you spend to buy it back?

273
00:17:43,210 --> 00:17:44,090
Not much.

274
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:47,170
Didn't I get that project bonus?

275
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,520
Along with the previous

276
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:50,640
earnings from being a designated driver, and what's left in my card.

277
00:17:51,210 --> 00:17:53,000
